Northern Rock to Hire Morgan Stanley to Advise on Possible Sale

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-02-17T19:37:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/northern-rock-to-hire-morgan-stanley-to-advise-on-possible-sale.html
Northern Rock Plc and U.K. Financial
Investments Ltd are set to appoint Morgan Stanley to advise the
government on “strategic options” regarding the possible sale
of the lender to the private sector, Sky News City Editor Mark
Kleinman  reported , citing people close to the process.  While a sale is not imminent and “there is no fixed
timetable,” the appointment of an adviser indicates that the
process may be about to start, Kleinman said without
attribution.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 